# Notes System

Notes are the user's personal knowledge layer in LexMastery.

They extend learning beyond consumption.

---

# Product Vision

Notes must:

- capture insights during learning
- link directly to lessons and concepts
- support AI summarization
- enable revision and recall

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

NotesController (Riverpod)

↓

NotesState

↓

NotesRepository

↓

Local DB + Sync Service

---

# State Management

NotesState includes:

- loading
- saved
- syncing
- error

Core Data:

- noteContent
- linkedLessonId
- tags
- timestamps
- AI summaries

---

# Note Types

- Lesson Notes
- AI-generated Notes
- Manual Notes
- Revision Notes

---

# Editing Rules

Notes must support:

- rich text editing
- highlight linking
- inline tagging
- auto-save

---

# AI Integration

AI can:

- summarize notes
- expand explanations
- generate revision summaries
- link related concepts

---

# Navigation Rules

Notes accessible from:

- Lesson Player
- Dashboard
- Profile
- AI Tutor

---

# Offline Behaviour

- full offline editing
- sync when online
- conflict resolution supported

---

# API Contracts

GET /notes

POST /notes/create

PUT /notes/update

DELETE /notes/delete

POST /notes/sync

---

# Analytics Events

note_created

note_updated

note_deleted

note_ai_summary_generated

---

# UI Composition Rules

Notes UI must include:

- editor view
- note list
- tag filters
- linked lesson indicator
- AI assist button

---

# UX Rules

- auto-save every change
- no manual save button required
- keep writing flow uninterrupted

---

# Error Handling

- local persistence must prevent data loss
- retry sync silently

---

# Performance

- instant typing response
- debounce sync operations

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader editing support
- keyboard shortcuts
- readable formatting

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Note CRUD logic

Sync engine

AI summarization

Widget Tests:

Editor UI

Note list UI

Integration Tests:

Full note lifecycle

Offline editing flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating notes:

- always use auto-save
- always support offline editing
- always link notes to lessons
- never interrupt writing flow